                            <comment id="14478564" author="berni_huber" created="Fri, 12 Jun 2009 02:05:00 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Failing testcase as it assumes that PropertyChangeListener for prop &apos;model&apos; is auto-removed via&lt;br/&gt;
SwingBuilder.dispose&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14468293" author="amir75" created="Sat, 28 Nov 2009 03:13:10 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;There&apos;s a typo in this method which has carried through versions 1.5-1.7&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Class: groovy.swing.factory.TableModelFactory&lt;br/&gt;
Method: onNodeCompleted(...)&lt;br/&gt;
This line:&lt;br/&gt;
  builder.addDisposalClosure( &lt;/p&gt;
{parent.removeProppertyChangeListener(&apos;table&apos;, listener)}
&lt;p&gt;)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;(See the double p in propperty)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&apos;parent&apos; is a JTable object, and the typo is occasionally causing MissingMethodExceptions.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The typo is shown in the title of this &apos;issue&apos;, but I just wanted to clarify it&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Best,&lt;br/&gt;
Amir&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14478776" author="paulk" created="Sat, 5 Dec 2009 05:11:48 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed in trunk&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14478769" author="paulk" created="Sat, 5 Dec 2009 05:29:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;fixed in 1_6_X and 1_7_X branches&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14478767" author="paulk" created="Sat, 5 Dec 2009 05:32:51 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;previous two comments relate to &quot;propperty typo&quot; being fixed - I haven&apos;t tested yet, so if there may still be a need to change &apos;table&apos; to &apos;model&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14480517" author="paulk" created="Sun, 27 Apr 2014 00:02:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;As far as I can tell, &apos;table&apos; was changed to &apos;model&apos; back in the 1.7 timeframes, so I&apos;ll mark this as resolved. Please reopen if you spot any problems.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
